               <p>Organized into two subseries: Correspondence and Estate Papers.</p>
            </arrangement>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_e695fe747c684f0d7223c89127b179a6">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Family correspondence addresses not only family matters such as health and welfare, personal financial situations, and births and deaths of family members, but also legal and economic topics related to the conditions in and prospects of the Dakota Territory and South Dakota. Estate papers document the holdings and distribution of the property of Fisk's parents, John F. and Elizabeth S.Fisk.</p>
            </scopecontent>
